WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
- He wants out.
- Varga stays.

2
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
I quit Schweikart and Cokely.

3
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
- Wait. What?
- To help people who are actually in need.

4
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
Put your phone down. Leave it on.

5
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
What did you do. Saul?

6
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
If you don't trust your
men with your money.

7
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.412
you have bigger problems than
if you trust Saul Goodman.

8
00:00:00.414 --> 00:00:02.547
Come on. Ignacio. go.

9
00:00:02.549 --> 00:00:05.349
We got a long way ahead of us.

10
00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:13.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

11
00:01:04.205 --> 00:01:06.685
Hey. Did you hear all that?

12
00:01:06.687 --> 00:01:09.368
I heard enough to
know she saved your ass.

13
00:01:09.370 --> 00:01:11.372
So... ?

14
00:01:12.322 --> 00:01:15.283
So what happens next?

15
00:01:15.285 --> 00:01:16.564
We'll see.

16
00:01:22.972 --> 00:01:24.974
Who was that?

17
00:01:26.536 --> 00:01:31.178
Uh. that was. um...

18
00:01:31.180 --> 00:01:33.580
It's the guy who saved my life.

19
00:01:33.582 --> 00:01:35.862
Kim. I got the money.

20
00:01:35.864 --> 00:01:38.345
I was on my way back...

21
00:01:38.347 --> 00:01:40.349
I thought I was home free...

22
00:01:42.351 --> 00:01:49.275
And I was ambushed.
by. uh. like. a gang.

23
00:01:49.277 --> 00:01:52.678
A... A cartel gang.

24
00:01:52.680 --> 00:01:55.201
And they... they took the money.

25
00:01:55.203 --> 00:01:58.524
and one of them...

26
00:01:58.526 --> 00:02:00.966
put a gun to my head.

27
00:02:03.899 --> 00:02:06.219
And that guy on the phone... ?

28
00:02:06.221 --> 00:02:07.700
He showed up.

29
00:02:07.702 --> 00:02:10.583
He... He shot 'em with a sniper rifle.

30
00:02:10.585 --> 00:02:14.549
He... killed all of them.

31
00:02:15.309 --> 00:02:17.429
All but one.

32
00:02:17.431 --> 00:02:20.392
One guy got away.

33
00:02:20.394 --> 00:02:24.599
And later. I helped him
to get that one. too.

34
00:02:25.559 --> 00:02:26.798
Kim. I...

35
00:02:26.800 --> 00:02:28.039
Jimmy. Jimmy. Jimmy.

36
00:02:28.041 --> 00:02:30.161
Oh. my God.

37
00:02:30.163 --> 00:02:32.283
Oh. my God.

38
00:02:36.850 --> 00:02:39.252
I think we should get outta here.

39
00:02:47.580 --> 00:02:50.660
Kind of assumed we'd
be staying at a Motel 6

40
00:02:50.662 --> 00:02:52.182
or the nail salon.

41
00:02:52.184 --> 00:02:54.664
B-Better to have more people around.

42
00:03:30.185 --> 00:03:33.346
How're your shoulders?

43
00:03:33.348 --> 00:03:34.988
Should I put something on them.

44
00:03:34.990 --> 00:03:36.629
or would that just make it worse?

45
00:03:38.914 --> 00:03:43.037
I think I'm. uh...

46
00:03:46.961 --> 00:03:49.604
Am I bad for you?

47
00:03:53.167 --> 00:03:56.448
Are you "bad for me"?

48
00:03:56.450 --> 00:04:00.011
I got you into this.

49
00:04:00.013 --> 00:04:02.734
What happened tonight...

50
00:04:02.736 --> 00:04:04.776
None of this would have happened

51
00:04:04.778 --> 00:04:06.780
if you weren't with me.

52
00:04:28.440 --> 00:04:30.442
You crossed a line.

53
00:04:34.285 --> 00:04:36.287
You're not gonna do it again.

54
00:04:40.571 --> 00:04:43.494
Yeah.

55
00:04:46.257 --> 00:04:48.497
It's been a long day.

56
00:04:48.499 --> 00:04:50.621
Come on. Make room.

57
00:04:52.262 --> 00:04:54.264
Mm.

58
00:05:08.718 --> 00:05:10.357
Good night.

59
00:06:05.541 --> 00:06:07.060
Well?

60
00:06:07.062 --> 00:06:09.342
He went over the border and kept going.

61
00:06:09.344 --> 00:06:12.065
Looks to be headed for
his place in Chihuahua.

62
00:06:12.067 --> 00:06:14.347
And he should be there in a few hours.

63
00:06:14.349 --> 00:06:15.628
Good.

64
00:06:15.630 --> 00:06:17.390
There's a wrinkle.

65
00:06:17.392 --> 00:06:19.592
He took Varga with him.

66
00:06:19.594 --> 00:06:21.113
Why?

67
00:06:22.677 --> 00:06:24.597
Well. if he thought Varga
was working for you.

68
00:06:24.599 --> 00:06:26.078
he'd have killed him on the spot.

69
00:06:26.080 --> 00:06:27.679
If I had to guess.

70
00:06:27.681 --> 00:06:31.483
I'd say Varga's up for a promotion.

71
00:06:31.485 --> 00:06:34.005
Can you communicate with Varga?

72
00:06:34.007 --> 00:06:37.449
Salamanca's place is in
the middle of nowhere.

73
00:06:37.451 --> 00:06:39.931
Landlines and sat phones only.

74
00:06:39.933 --> 00:06:42.453
A technical issue.

75
00:06:42.455 --> 00:06:44.455
The way things stand.

76
00:06:44.457 --> 00:06:47.258
he's gonna get caught in the crossfire.

77
00:06:47.260 --> 00:06:48.939
I'm thinking we should find a way

78
00:06:48.941 --> 00:06:52.062
to pull him out of there.

79
00:06:58.630 --> 00:07:01.273
And tip our hand?

80
00:07:02.915 --> 00:07:06.678
He's earned some consideration.

81
00:07:17.488 --> 00:07:18.887
Does Varga know

82
00:07:18.889 --> 00:07:20.889
there's going to be an assassination?

83
00:07:20.891 --> 00:07:22.331
No one's told him...

84
00:07:22.333 --> 00:07:24.693
but he can make a
pretty damn good guess.

85
00:07:24.695 --> 00:07:27.415
Perhaps...

86
00:07:27.417 --> 00:07:29.858
there is a way to make
use of this situation.

87
00:07:30.635 --> 00:07:33.298
The men I've chosen for
this are highly skilled.

88
00:07:33.300 --> 00:07:34.882
They're the best in the their business.

89
00:07:34.884 --> 00:07:38.866
But the one thing they do not have...

90
00:07:38.868 --> 00:07:41.511
is a man on the inside.

91
00:08:58.983 --> 00:09:01.824
Mi Yolis! Como estas?

92
00:09:01.826 --> 00:09:04.146
Quien te quiere?

93
00:09:04.148 --> 00:09:06.629
Te ves flaco.

94
00:09:06.631 --> 00:09:08.230
No había nada comer allá.

95
00:09:13.983 --> 00:09:15.517
¿Cecilio. cómo estás. amigo?

96
00:09:15.519 --> 00:09:17.919
Patrón...

97
00:09:19.523 --> 00:09:21.282
Ah.

98
00:09:26.449 --> 00:09:28.209
Nachito. come on over. huh?

99
00:09:28.211 --> 00:09:29.250
Don't be shy.

100
00:09:37.499 --> 00:09:39.659
These... These are my people.

101
00:09:39.661 --> 00:09:42.022
Yolanda... she is the best
cook in all of Chihua...

102
00:09:42.024 --> 00:09:45.825
you're gonna eat like you have
never eaten before in your life.

103
00:09:45.827 --> 00:09:48.989
Cecilio... he takes care
of all of my gardens...

104
00:09:51.364 --> 00:09:53.633
His tomatoes are the best ever. eh?

105
00:09:53.635 --> 00:09:57.396
Ciro. Miguel. Gerardo. Raúl.

106
00:09:57.398 --> 00:09:59.598
and all the rest of these fools...

107
00:09:59.600 --> 00:10:02.321
they're supposed to
be guarding this place.

108
00:10:02.323 --> 00:10:05.000
but. uh. I just keep 'em around

109
00:10:05.002 --> 00:10:06.805
because they're so pretty. right?

110
00:10:09.129 --> 00:10:10.809
Ah.

111
00:10:13.253 --> 00:10:15.277
Eh?

112
00:10:24.544 --> 00:10:25.783
Hey. listen.

113
00:10:25.785 --> 00:10:27.144
Welcome. Smile.

114
00:10:27.146 --> 00:10:28.866
You're in my house. man.
Come on. Come in.

115
00:10:47.846 --> 00:10:49.847
Mnh.

116
00:10:58.976 --> 00:11:02.097
Hey. did you pack
anything with aloe in it?

117
00:11:02.099 --> 00:11:03.819
Oh. Mornin'.

118
00:11:03.821 --> 00:11:05.820
Morning.

119
00:11:05.822 --> 00:11:09.103
- I didn't wake you. did I?
- No.

120
00:11:09.105 --> 00:11:11.084
- Uh. you're going to court?
- Yeah.

121
00:11:11.086 --> 00:11:12.509
I have a hearing at 10:00.

122
00:11:12.511 --> 00:11:14.463
and I want to see if I can catch Oakley

123
00:11:14.465 --> 00:11:17.712
before I go in.

124
00:11:17.714 --> 00:11:19.874
You seemed like you could use the sleep.

125
00:11:19.876 --> 00:11:21.715
Yeah.

126
00:11:32.937 --> 00:11:35.320
Hey. I think I might have a better idea.

127
00:11:35.322 --> 00:11:37.506
What if we spend the
whole day here. you know?

128
00:11:37.508 --> 00:11:39.410
Uh. this place has got everything.

129
00:11:39.412 --> 00:11:42.215
It's got a heated pool.
a swim-up bar. a hot tub.

130
00:11:42.217 --> 00:11:43.696
Well. I didn't pack a swimsuit.

131
00:11:43.698 --> 00:11:45.057
Neither did I.

132
00:11:45.059 --> 00:11:46.699
Th-There's a shop downstairs.

133
00:11:46.701 --> 00:11:49.061
And... And... And we can
stop in at the spa. you know.

134
00:11:49.063 --> 00:11:50.743
a-and get couples massages.

135
00:11:50.745 --> 00:11:52.384
With your sunburn?

136
00:11:52.386 --> 00:11:54.426
Yeah.

137
00:11:54.428 --> 00:11:56.825
Or. um. or a "seaweed wrap". you know.

138
00:11:56.827 --> 00:11:58.574
and then... then we'll just go hang

139
00:11:58.576 --> 00:12:00.552
in the co-ed sauna. you know.

140
00:12:00.554 --> 00:12:03.034
- sweat out some toxins and. uh...
- Mm.

141
00:12:03.036 --> 00:12:04.435
Oh!

142
00:12:04.437 --> 00:12:06.357
24-hour room service.

143
00:12:06.359 --> 00:12:08.202
Hey. what could be more luxurious

144
00:12:08.204 --> 00:12:11.225
than to spend a whole
day being totally pampered

145
00:12:11.227 --> 00:12:14.191
and end it all with a
midnight cheeseburger?

146
00:12:14.193 --> 00:12:16.407
Come on. Hey. don't we deserve this?

147
00:12:16.409 --> 00:12:19.129
Jimmy. I-I-I have clients.

148
00:12:19.131 --> 00:12:20.450
Yeah.

149
00:12:20.452 --> 00:12:22.209
You... You just quit Schweikart.

150
00:12:22.211 --> 00:12:23.713
I mean. take one day off.

151
00:12:23.715 --> 00:12:24.998
The clerks love you.

152
00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:27.138
They will give you a
continuance on anything.

153
00:12:27.140 --> 00:12:29.299
Hey. Kim. we already
sprang for this place.

154
00:12:29.301 --> 00:12:31.341
I'm just sayin' let's take advantage.

155
00:12:31.343 --> 00:12:33.983
You know. let's John
and Yoko this sucker.

156
00:12:33.985 --> 00:12:35.987
You don't think it's safe?

157
00:12:38.790 --> 00:12:39.869
Probably. it is.

158
00:12:39.871 --> 00:12:43.502
But here's the thing.

159
00:12:43.504 --> 00:12:45.647
L-Lalo has guys. right?

160
00:12:45.649 --> 00:12:47.756
So it doesn't really
matter where he is...

161
00:12:47.758 --> 00:12:49.971
if he finds one loose end.

162
00:12:49.973 --> 00:12:52.175
all it takes is a phone call.

163
00:12:53.844 --> 00:12:55.764
Do you know something
you're not telling me?

164
00:12:55.766 --> 00:12:57.466
No. No. I don't.

165
00:12:57.468 --> 00:13:01.769
But what's the harm in
being a little cautious?

166
00:13:01.771 --> 00:13:03.891
What about tomorrow?

167
00:13:03.893 --> 00:13:06.093
And the next day?

168
00:13:06.095 --> 00:13:08.455
Jimmy. what about next week?

169
00:13:08.457 --> 00:13:11.340
I don't know.

170
00:13:14.303 --> 00:13:16.783
Alright.

171
00:13:16.785 --> 00:13:18.785
Then. the way I see it.

172
00:13:18.787 --> 00:13:20.667
we just need to keep our eyes open

173
00:13:20.669 --> 00:13:23.349
and get on with our lives.

174
00:13:23.351 --> 00:13:25.271
- Kim. listen...
- The courthouse...

175
00:13:25.273 --> 00:13:28.114
it's... it's three blocks from here.

176
00:13:28.116 --> 00:13:30.436
It's full of cops...

177
00:13:30.438 --> 00:13:34.080
police headquarters is right next door.

178
00:13:34.082 --> 00:13:38.764
Jimmy...

179
00:13:38.766 --> 00:13:40.405
it's gonna be fine.

180
00:13:40.407 --> 00:13:42.409
I'll see you later.

181
00:14:10.275 --> 00:14:13.076
Hey. it's me. I want an update.

182
00:14:14.119 --> 00:14:15.558
Bullshit.

183
00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:19.162
I want to know what's going on.

184
00:14:19.164 --> 00:14:20.523
Not good enough.

185
00:14:20.525 --> 00:14:22.165
No. You know what?

186
00:14:22.167 --> 00:14:24.487
Y'know what... We are...
We are gonna talk about this

187
00:14:24.489 --> 00:14:25.848
face-to-face.

188
00:14:25.850 --> 00:14:27.410
You tell me where you are.

189
00:14:27.412 --> 00:14:28.571
I will come to...

190
00:14:28.573 --> 00:14:30.012
Hello?

191
00:14:39.537 --> 00:14:41.417
That means we won.

192
00:14:41.419 --> 00:14:43.859
The state dropped the charges.

193
00:14:43.861 --> 00:14:44.980
No. no. no.

194
00:14:44.982 --> 00:14:46.622
You don't have to appear in court again.

195
00:14:46.624 --> 00:14:49.266
Now we both have the morning off.

196
00:14:51.508 --> 00:14:54.709
Uh-huh.

197
00:14:54.711 --> 00:14:57.111
Mm-hmm.

198
00:14:57.113 --> 00:14:58.713
I'm sorry. Mira... you know what?

199
00:14:58.715 --> 00:15:00.434
I have to go.

200
00:15:00.436 --> 00:15:03.157
But call if you have
any questions. any time.

201
00:15:03.159 --> 00:15:05.319
Okay. Yes. bye.

202
00:15:05.321 --> 00:15:06.480
Hey. Grant.

203
00:15:06.482 --> 00:15:07.962
You got a minute?

204
00:15:07.964 --> 00:15:09.707
How's it going?

205
00:15:09.709 --> 00:15:10.844
Uh. let's see.

206
00:15:10.846 --> 00:15:13.799
I have half an hour to
plead out four taggers

207
00:15:13.801 --> 00:15:15.791
and a homeless guy who tried to stuff

208
00:15:15.793 --> 00:15:18.692
a dozen hardboiled eggs down
his pants at a Ruby Tuesday's.

209
00:15:18.694 --> 00:15:21.334
Life in the Public Defender's office.
How's your day so far?

210
00:15:21.336 --> 00:15:24.017
Uh. I've got some holes in
my schedule I'm lookin' to fill.

211
00:15:24.019 --> 00:15:26.703
Holes? You tellin' me
you're billin'... what?

212
00:15:26.705 --> 00:15:27.740
Two-fifty an hour?

213
00:15:27.742 --> 00:15:29.462
And you've got holes in your schedule?

214
00:15:29.464 --> 00:15:31.664
If I were you. I'd keep things airtight.

215
00:15:31.666 --> 00:15:34.346
I'd like some more PD overflow.

216
00:15:34.348 --> 00:15:36.388
Go talk to the contract liaison.

217
00:15:36.390 --> 00:15:38.190
And Gloria'll set you up.

218
00:15:38.192 --> 00:15:39.791
Alright. the thing is.

219
00:15:39.793 --> 00:15:41.626
I know I'm not supposed
to choose the cases I get.

220
00:15:41.628 --> 00:15:45.720
but I'm looking for
something... specific.

221
00:15:47.160 --> 00:15:48.760
Specific?

222
00:15:48.762 --> 00:15:50.041
Like what?

223
00:15:50.043 --> 00:15:52.964
Uh. uh.

224
00:15:52.966 --> 00:15:54.843
I just want to make sure
I'm spending my time

225
00:15:54.845 --> 00:15:57.648
where it'll do the most good.

226
00:15:57.650 --> 00:15:59.089
I gotcha.

227
00:15:59.091 --> 00:16:02.453
So plain old indigent's
not good enough for you?

228
00:16:02.455 --> 00:16:06.176
You want the clients that'll
get you. you know. in here.

229
00:16:06.178 --> 00:16:09.059
Grant. just let me
have some tricky ones.

230
00:16:09.061 --> 00:16:10.744
Think of all the extra time you'll have

231
00:16:10.746 --> 00:16:12.546
to spend on your egg stuffers.

232
00:16:13.309 --> 00:16:15.932
If I were going to go along with that.

233
00:16:15.934 --> 00:16:18.267
- you'd have to take felonies.
- Sure.

234
00:16:18.269 --> 00:16:20.189
We're talking cases that
are headed for trial.

235
00:16:20.191 --> 00:16:22.013
Nothing you can plead
out in three hot minutes

236
00:16:22.015 --> 00:16:23.472
with your friendly neighborhood ADA.

237
00:16:23.474 --> 00:16:24.794
I'll take 20.

238
00:16:24.796 --> 00:16:26.075
Today.

239
00:16:26.077 --> 00:16:28.157
20?

240
00:16:28.159 --> 00:16:29.838
That's your offer?

241
00:16:29.840 --> 00:16:31.800
20 felonies?

242
00:16:31.802 --> 00:16:33.522
Yes.

243
00:16:33.524 --> 00:16:36.046
Hold this.

244
00:16:38.809 --> 00:16:40.048
Come on.

245
00:16:40.050 --> 00:16:41.209
Hey. Dana!

246
00:16:41.211 --> 00:16:42.493
Any chance you can tell the judge

247
00:16:42.495 --> 00:16:44.080
I'm running 15 minutes late?

248
00:16:45.775 --> 00:16:47.815
Oh. Gotta warn you. right now.

249
00:16:47.817 --> 00:16:50.498
we're backed up like an
outhouse at Woodstock.

250
00:16:57.452 --> 00:17:00.147
So. possession raps are here...

251
00:17:00.149 --> 00:17:01.948
Possession with intent...

252
00:17:01.950 --> 00:17:04.471
These are all assault...

253
00:17:04.473 --> 00:17:06.633
wait. no...

254
00:17:06.635 --> 00:17:08.831
assault's on the other
side of this shelf.

255
00:17:08.833 --> 00:17:10.717
All of these cases are pending?

256
00:17:10.719 --> 00:17:12.558
Pretty much.

257
00:17:12.560 --> 00:17:15.561
Had more burnouts than
usual this last quarter.

258
00:17:15.563 --> 00:17:18.356
That's what I call taking
that private firm gig.

259
00:17:18.358 --> 00:17:20.206
gettin' that sweet company car.

260
00:17:20.208 --> 00:17:22.209
burnin' rubber on your way out.

261
00:17:25.332 --> 00:17:29.534
Public intoxication. petty larceny.

262
00:17:29.536 --> 00:17:34.441
destruction of property.
DUI. trespassing...

263
00:17:35.702 --> 00:17:38.743
Involuntary manslaughter.

264
00:17:38.745 --> 00:17:43.147
immigration. domestic violence...

265
00:17:45.551 --> 00:17:49.273
Or. if you feel like you do want...

266
00:17:50.876 --> 00:17:52.676
Juveniles.

267
00:17:55.240 --> 00:17:56.880
Go ahead and have a look around.

268
00:17:56.882 --> 00:17:58.882
Let me know which ones you
want so we can kick 'em over.

269
00:17:58.884 --> 00:18:00.563
I'll getchu a box.

270
00:18:24.668 --> 00:18:26.750
Flashlight.

271
00:18:30.433 --> 00:18:34.355
When you talk to the
boss. you call him Don.

272
00:18:34.357 --> 00:18:36.717
He asks you a question.

273
00:18:36.719 --> 00:18:38.799
you tell the truth.

274
00:18:38.801 --> 00:18:43.043
fewest words... you can.

275
00:18:44.807 --> 00:18:46.767
If he likes you. he's gonna
give you a bump up.

276
00:18:49.932 --> 00:18:53.373
Hey. don't think I don't see you. eh?

277
00:18:53.375 --> 00:18:55.655
I see you. I do.

278
00:18:55.657 --> 00:18:59.581
Right now. steady is
what we need. you know?

279
00:19:02.063 --> 00:19:04.385
What if he doesn't like me?

280
00:19:06.988 --> 00:19:09.348
Ah. you'll be fine.

281
00:19:09.350 --> 00:19:10.949
Gimme the socket wrench.

282
00:19:21.922 --> 00:19:24.923
- Um. I gotta hit the head.
- Yeah. yeah.

283
00:19:26.566 --> 00:19:28.166
Hey. don't get any
grease on my sink. eh?

284
00:19:43.622 --> 00:19:45.302
Yeah.

285
00:20:24.871 --> 00:20:27.031
After that. I want you
both to be thinking about

286
00:20:27.033 --> 00:20:28.272
how to parse out discovery.

287
00:20:28.274 --> 00:20:29.833
It's gonna be document heavy.

288
00:20:29.835 --> 00:20:32.476
so let's be mindful
of resource management.

289
00:20:32.478 --> 00:20:34.558
Howard.

290
00:20:34.560 --> 00:20:36.239
Kim. Good to see you.

291
00:20:36.241 --> 00:20:38.644
- Uh. what floor?
- Three. please.

292
00:20:41.967 --> 00:20:43.286
Have you met my associates.

293
00:20:43.288 --> 00:20:44.927
Paul Shepard and Michelle Avila?

294
00:20:44.929 --> 00:20:46.569
- I don't think so. Hi.
- Hello.

295
00:20:46.571 --> 00:20:48.573
Nice to meet you.

296
00:20:50.134 --> 00:20:51.854
Uh. guys. this is Kim Wexler.

297
00:20:51.856 --> 00:20:53.455
She's an HHM alum

298
00:20:53.457 --> 00:20:55.577
and now heads up banking
at Schweikart and Cokely.

299
00:20:55.579 --> 00:20:57.581
Nice to meet you both.

300
00:21:01.505 --> 00:21:04.306
I'm actually not at Schweikart anymore.

301
00:21:04.308 --> 00:21:07.108
Or in banking. for that matter.

302
00:21:07.110 --> 00:21:08.590
Really?

303
00:21:08.592 --> 00:21:10.992
As of yesterday.

304
00:21:10.994 --> 00:21:12.996
Take care. Howard.

305
00:21:15.879 --> 00:21:17.438
Kim. Kim!

306
00:21:17.440 --> 00:21:19.442
Hang on a sec!

307
00:21:20.323 --> 00:21:22.763
Out of curiosity. where'd you land?

308
00:21:22.765 --> 00:21:23.964
Reeves and Green?

309
00:21:23.966 --> 00:21:26.730
I'm out on my own again.

310
00:21:26.732 --> 00:21:28.465
Rich let you go?

311
00:21:28.467 --> 00:21:30.690
It wasn't up to him. I left.

312
00:21:30.692 --> 00:21:32.332
What about Mesa Verde?

313
00:21:32.334 --> 00:21:34.654
I advised them to stay with Schweikart.

314
00:21:34.656 --> 00:21:38.137
Um. I know it's a
personal question. Kim.

315
00:21:38.139 --> 00:21:40.899
- but can I ask why?
- That is personal.

316
00:21:40.901 --> 00:21:42.742
- And I have a busy day. so...
- Spare me a minute.

317
00:21:42.744 --> 00:21:44.704
Please.

318
00:21:44.706 --> 00:21:46.707
It's important.

319
00:21:48.189 --> 00:21:52.311
What's up?

320
00:21:54.915 --> 00:21:57.956
I wasn't going to say anything.

321
00:21:57.958 --> 00:22:00.038
Last time I tried to get
something off my chest.

322
00:22:00.040 --> 00:22:01.159
it didn't go very well.

323
00:22:01.161 --> 00:22:03.841
I just think

324
00:22:03.843 --> 00:22:07.965
before you make any big
changes in your life.

325
00:22:07.967 --> 00:22:12.172
there's something about
Jimmy you ought to hear.

326
00:22:13.693 --> 00:22:15.695
Okay.

327
00:22:17.136 --> 00:22:20.817
A little while ago. I offered
Jimmy a job at HHM.

328
00:22:20.819 --> 00:22:23.300
I'm guessing he didn't
mention it to you.

329
00:22:26.305 --> 00:22:29.666
He said he had to think about it.

330
00:22:29.668 --> 00:22:32.228
But then. the very next night.

331
00:22:32.230 --> 00:22:34.911
he threw bowling balls
over my front gate.

332
00:22:34.913 --> 00:22:37.153
Bowling balls?

333
00:22:37.155 --> 00:22:39.198
Someone could've been really hurt.

334
00:22:39.200 --> 00:22:41.517
More or less destroyed my car.

335
00:22:41.519 --> 00:22:43.479
Then. a couple of weeks later.

336
00:22:43.481 --> 00:22:45.561
I'm having lunch with Cliff Main.

337
00:22:45.563 --> 00:22:48.483
and I'm accosted by two prostitutes.

338
00:22:48.485 --> 00:22:50.886
Actual prostitutes.

339
00:22:50.888 --> 00:22:53.248
Jimmy had sent them to make a scene.

340
00:22:53.250 --> 00:22:56.010
I confronted Jimmy about it.

341
00:22:56.012 --> 00:22:59.173
and after some hemming and hawing.

342
00:22:59.175 --> 00:23:01.177
he all but confessed.

343
00:23:07.703 --> 00:23:10.904
- And that's it?
- Mm-hmm.

344
00:23:10.906 --> 00:23:12.826
Sorry.

345
00:23:14.950 --> 00:23:17.230
Ah.

346
00:23:17.232 --> 00:23:19.913
Howard. you really...

347
00:23:19.915 --> 00:23:21.715
you... you really had me going there.

348
00:23:21.717 --> 00:23:24.157
Laugh if you want.

349
00:23:24.159 --> 00:23:25.958
but no person in their right mind

350
00:23:25.960 --> 00:23:27.640
would behave the way Jimmy has.

351
00:23:27.642 --> 00:23:29.041
We are talking about someone

352
00:23:29.043 --> 00:23:31.484
who's not in control of himself.

353
00:23:31.486 --> 00:23:34.311
You and I both know it makes no sense

354
00:23:34.313 --> 00:23:36.649
to drop a client like Mesa Verde.

355
00:23:36.651 --> 00:23:38.813
and I gotta think Jimmy had
something to do with that.

356
00:23:40.534 --> 00:23:45.177
Do you have any idea
how insulting that is?

357
00:23:45.179 --> 00:23:48.700
I make my own decisions.
for my own reasons.

358
00:23:48.702 --> 00:23:49.981
You gotta listen to me.

359
00:23:49.983 --> 00:23:51.542
The man needs help.

360
00:23:51.544 --> 00:23:55.188
Howard. I know Jimmy. and you're wrong.

361
00:24:00.833 --> 00:24:03.994
You know who really knew Jimmy?

362
00:24:03.996 --> 00:24:05.998
Chuck.

363
00:24:19.455 --> 00:24:22.938
Open up. asshole!

364
00:24:24.914 --> 00:24:26.634
Open this door!

365
00:24:26.636 --> 00:24:28.596
I want to talk to you!

366
00:24:37.366 --> 00:24:39.006
What? Huh?

367
00:24:39.008 --> 00:24:42.129
You didn't think I'd find
your ultra secret bat cave?

368
00:24:42.131 --> 00:24:43.650
Well. the joke's on you. sucker!

369
00:24:43.652 --> 00:24:44.794
I'm your attorney.

370
00:24:44.796 --> 00:24:47.854
and you will let me in!

371
00:24:57.305 --> 00:24:58.944
I'm not goin' anywhere!

372
00:24:58.946 --> 00:25:00.105
I mean it!

373
00:25:00.107 --> 00:25:02.227
I got nowhere to be!

374
00:25:02.229 --> 00:25:04.269
Open. Up. Now!

375
00:25:04.271 --> 00:25:06.273
Hey!

376
00:25:07.114 --> 00:25:08.994
What the hell do you think you're doing?

377
00:25:08.996 --> 00:25:10.635
Ah. there he is!

378
00:25:10.637 --> 00:25:13.518
Not... Not a fan of the
surprise pop-in. huh?

379
00:25:13.520 --> 00:25:15.920
- Well. I can't imagine why!
- You keep it down.

380
00:25:15.922 --> 00:25:17.642
- I got neighbors.
- I will not keep it down.

381
00:25:17.644 --> 00:25:19.444
I want answers. okay?

382
00:25:19.446 --> 00:25:21.525
The time has come for
you to level with me.

383
00:25:21.527 --> 00:25:23.447
and I'm not going to leave until you do.

384
00:25:23.449 --> 00:25:24.929
Inside. now.

385
00:25:24.931 --> 00:25:26.250
Okay. look. look.

386
00:25:26.252 --> 00:25:28.372
Okay.

387
00:25:30.256 --> 00:25:34.217
Y-You saved my life.

388
00:25:34.219 --> 00:25:35.499
Thank you for that.

389
00:25:36.902 --> 00:25:38.024
But from here on out.

390
00:25:38.026 --> 00:25:40.583
I gotta be kept in the loop. man.

391
00:25:40.585 --> 00:25:42.889
It's not my fault that I got ambushed.

392
00:25:42.891 --> 00:25:46.349
Why did I have to lie
to Salamanca about that?

393
00:25:46.351 --> 00:25:48.033
