we replace it with sunblock.

538
00:40:01.428 --> 00:40:03.330
He gets in his tanning bed.

539
00:40:03.332 --> 00:40:05.985
and waste of time.

540
00:40:05.987 --> 00:40:10.470
Or... Or...

541
00:40:10.472 --> 00:40:12.792
Or what?

542
00:40:12.794 --> 00:40:16.155
We'd never do it. but...

543
00:40:18.039 --> 00:40:21.680
Never do what?

544
00:40:21.682 --> 00:40:24.325
What if...

545
00:40:26.166 --> 00:40:29.609
What if Howard does something terrible?

546
00:40:31.242 --> 00:40:34.906
Like he murders a waiter

547
00:40:34.908 --> 00:40:36.974
for putting butter
on his cauliflower... ?

548
00:40:38.258 --> 00:40:42.259
No. I mean really bad.

549
00:40:42.261 --> 00:40:44.913
Like misconduct.

550
00:40:44.915 --> 00:40:46.618
You know. misappropriating funds

551
00:40:46.620 --> 00:40:49.679
and. um. bribing witnesses...

552
00:40:49.681 --> 00:40:51.303
something like that.

553
00:40:51.305 --> 00:40:54.511
You know what that'd mean
for the Sandpiper case?

554
00:40:54.513 --> 00:40:56.953
A big class action suit?

555
00:40:56.955 --> 00:40:59.516
It could tank the whole thing.

556
00:41:00.839 --> 00:41:03.279
Cliff Main's hair would be on fire.

557
00:41:05.283 --> 00:41:07.683
He'd get it settled.

558
00:41:07.685 --> 00:41:09.887
Pronto.

559
00:41:11.969 --> 00:41:13.849
He would?

560
00:41:13.851 --> 00:41:15.290
Yeah.

561
00:41:15.292 --> 00:41:19.497
Think about how much
they've put into that case.

562
00:41:20.297 --> 00:41:24.287
Almost two years of work.

563
00:41:24.289 --> 00:41:27.513
If it fell apart now.
they'd get nothing.

564
00:41:27.515 --> 00:41:29.195
So. yeah.

565
00:41:29.197 --> 00:41:31.477
Cliff Main would take whatever
Sandpiper was offering.

566
00:41:31.479 --> 00:41:34.600
I already tried like hell
to get Sandpiper settled.

567
00:41:34.602 --> 00:41:36.122
Yeah. but you went about it wrong.

568
00:41:38.005 --> 00:41:41.649
Sorry. but... this is how you do it.

569
00:41:46.093 --> 00:41:48.493
And it's not like the
old folks'd get stiffed.

570
00:41:48.495 --> 00:41:50.415
If Sandpiper settled now.

571
00:41:50.417 --> 00:41:54.659
they might each get 15. 20 bucks less.

572
00:41:54.661 --> 00:41:59.383
but they'd get their money now.
while they can still use it.

573
00:41:59.385 --> 00:42:03.747
And the lawyers get paid.

574
00:42:03.749 --> 00:42:05.751
And the lawyers get paid.

575
00:42:07.713 --> 00:42:09.875
How much of the common fund do you get?

576
00:42:12.478 --> 00:42:16.682
We get 20% of the common fund.

577
00:42:18.643 --> 00:42:20.523
I'm just... I'm...

578
00:42:20.525 --> 00:42:22.485
Forget it. okay?

579
00:42:22.487 --> 00:42:24.967
Okay.

580
00:44:12.114 --> 00:44:14.033
Hey.

581
00:44:14.035 --> 00:44:16.676
Hey.

582
00:44:16.678 --> 00:44:18.958
Have a seat.

583
00:44:40.373 --> 00:44:42.653
Hey. you did good today. huh?

584
00:44:42.655 --> 00:44:46.297
Tomorrow. I'll show you around. Mm.

585
00:44:46.299 --> 00:44:48.979
When you go back up north...

586
00:44:48.981 --> 00:44:51.221
you're gonna be halfway
to being a Salamanca. eh?

587
00:44:52.945 --> 00:44:54.224
Thanks.

588
00:44:58.944 --> 00:45:01.222
Ah.

589
00:45:01.224 --> 00:45:03.304
Another night owl. huh? You don't sleep?

590
00:45:03.306 --> 00:45:05.466
Mnh-mnh.

591
00:45:05.468 --> 00:45:09.790
Not tonight.

592
00:45:09.792 --> 00:45:13.754
Yeah. I never sleep much.

593
00:45:13.756 --> 00:45:15.555
An hour. maybe two.

594
00:45:15.557 --> 00:45:17.559
It's enough.

595
00:45:20.482 --> 00:45:22.484
When it's like this?

596
00:45:24.646 --> 00:45:26.648
That's when I can think.

597
00:45:28.730 --> 00:45:32.732
I get my best ideas when
everybody else is asleep.

598
00:45:34.735 --> 00:45:37.376
Some people... they call it a curse.

599
00:45:37.378 --> 00:45:39.738
I like it.

600
00:45:39.740 --> 00:45:43.341
I don't know.

601
00:45:45.505 --> 00:45:49.733
I'd rather get some shuteye.

602
00:45:49.735 --> 00:45:51.557
And yet. here we are.

603
00:46:03.362 --> 00:46:05.522
Got anything stronger?

604
00:46:06.966 --> 00:46:09.646
Now you're talking.

605
00:46:09.648 --> 00:46:14.130
In the bar. bottom shelf. decanter.

606
00:46:14.132 --> 00:46:16.653
That's the good stuff.

607
00:46:16.655 --> 00:46:18.975
Two glasses.

608
00:46:59.455 --> 00:47:01.054
There he is!

609
00:47:01.056 --> 00:47:03.176
I thought you got lost.

610
00:47:08.223 --> 00:47:09.622
Ah.

611
00:47:17.992 --> 00:47:20.593
You ever had Louis XIII?

612
00:47:20.595 --> 00:47:22.314
I don't think so.

613
00:47:22.316 --> 00:47:24.396
Ooph. You're in for a treat.

614
00:47:33.193 --> 00:47:36.714
To sleep and those who need it.

615
00:47:36.716 --> 00:47:38.275
To sleep.

616
00:47:44.323 --> 00:47:46.203
What the hell is that?

617
00:47:51.250 --> 00:47:54.250
These morons have no respect!

618
00:47:54.252 --> 00:47:56.172
iCiro!

619
00:48:56.030 --> 00:48:57.470
Ah!

620
00:48:57.472 --> 00:48:59.111
iCiro!

621
00:49:05.840 --> 00:49:07.863
iCiro!

622
00:49:11.454 --> 00:49:12.678
Ciro. Ciro.

623
00:52:37.171 --> 00:52:38.490
Ah!

624
00:53:26.817 --> 00:53:29.698
Ah.

625
00:53:29.302 --> 00:53:31.862
What do you want?

626
00:53:31.164 --> 00:53:33.646
I'll have a little of everything.

627
00:53:35.368 --> 00:53:37.850
Actually. leave off the mint chip.

628
00:53:44.456 --> 00:53:46.737
I set the alarm for 6:00.

629
00:53:46.739 --> 00:53:50.860
Since we have to check out
and go home before work.

630
00:53:50.862 --> 00:53:53.663
That's a solid 2 and a half hours.

631
00:53:53.665 --> 00:53:55.667
Sounds good.

632
00:54:12.683 --> 00:54:14.685
So. what would you do with it?

633
00:54:17.768 --> 00:54:19.327
I don't know.

634
00:54:19.329 --> 00:54:22.370
What would you?

635
00:54:22.372 --> 00:54:26.894
I'd hire Stef away from Schweikart.

636
00:54:26.896 --> 00:54:30.658
I'd hire Bruce from HHM.

637
00:54:30.660 --> 00:54:33.020
I'd get Viola.

638
00:54:33.022 --> 00:54:35.793
I'd rent the smallest. shittiest office

639
00:54:35.795 --> 00:54:37.304
I could find near the courthouse

640
00:54:37.306 --> 00:54:40.907
and open a pro bono practice.

641
00:54:40.909 --> 00:54:43.627
Give regular people the
kind of representation

642
00:54:43.629 --> 00:54:45.631
usually only millionaires get.

643
00:54:47.195 --> 00:54:49.235
I was gonna say we'd buy a house.

644
00:54:49.237 --> 00:54:51.397
Sorry.

645
00:54:51.399 --> 00:54:52.678
Yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah.

646
00:54:52.680 --> 00:54:55.281
We could do both.

647
00:54:55.283 --> 00:54:56.722
Last I heard.

648
00:54:56.724 --> 00:54:59.965
Sandpiper was willing
to go to $26 million.

649
00:54:59.967 --> 00:55:01.647
Wow.

650
00:55:01.649 --> 00:55:04.376
Um. a third of that is $8.5 million.

651
00:55:04.378 --> 00:55:06.241
Mm-hmm. And 20% of that is...

652
00:55:06.243 --> 00:55:08.245
Around $2 mil.

653
00:55:12.739 --> 00:55:17.101
Ah. but it's not happening.

654
00:55:17.103 --> 00:55:19.864
Come on. Kim.

655
00:55:19.866 --> 00:55:22.707
We're not talking
about a bar trick here.

656
00:55:22.709 --> 00:55:24.750
We're talking about scorched earth.

657
00:55:26.392 --> 00:55:28.672
We would have to hurt him.

658
00:55:28.674 --> 00:55:30.754
Hurt him bad.

659
00:55:30.756 --> 00:55:32.716
To get a bunch of lawyers
to run for the exits?

660
00:55:32.718 --> 00:55:37.080
Howard would have to have
done something... unforgivable.

661
00:55:37.082 --> 00:55:38.601
At the end of it.

662
00:55:38.603 --> 00:55:41.326
he might never be able
to practice law again.

663
00:55:42.447 --> 00:55:45.128
Ah. he doesn't deserve that.

664
00:55:45.130 --> 00:55:47.131
And who knows if we could pull it off?

665
00:55:49.934 --> 00:55:54.176
Okay. maybe we could pull it off. yeah.

666
00:55:54.178 --> 00:55:55.818
But we won't.

667
00:56:03.106 --> 00:56:07.909
We're talking about a career setback.

668
00:56:07.911 --> 00:56:11.514
A career setback for one lawyer.

669
00:56:13.436 --> 00:56:15.676
Yeah. and you could
help a lot of people.

670
00:56:15.678 --> 00:56:17.318
I-I get it. but...

671
00:56:20.323 --> 00:56:22.082
Kim. doing this. that...

672
00:56:23.365 --> 00:56:25.405
It's not you.

673
00:56:25.407 --> 00:56:27.888
Okay?

674
00:56:27.890 --> 00:56:30.370
You would not be okay with it.

675
00:56:30.372 --> 00:56:32.814
Not in the cold light of day.

676
00:56:35.977 --> 00:56:38.500
Wouldn't I?

677
00:56:48.669 --> 00:56:50.309
I'm gonna go take a shower

678
00:56:50.311 --> 00:56:52.633
so I don't have to in the morning.

679
00:56:55.916 --> 00:56:58.478
Kim. you're shittin' me. right?

680
00:57:00.080 --> 00:57:01.319
P-chew! P-chew!

681
00:58:16.552 --> 00:58:17.831
Bien.

682
00:58:17.833 --> 00:58:20.834
Bien.

683
00:58:33.487 --> 00:58:36.512
Bien. Bien. bien. bien. bien.

684
00:58:37.305 --> 00:59:37.781
